Possibly, upon doing some more research it appears this may be the best place to report it:  <https://github.com/uBlockOrigin/uBlock-issues/issues|https://github.com/uBlockOrigin/uBlock-issues/issues>

Fixing the problem at it's root cause is going to be better than any band aid done by HubSpot or you. It won't result in strange code and will be less likely to have a regression.
I guess you emptied the attachedStylesheets and attachedJS property and add it back manually from the interface

<@UEC65BQV8> Can you ask your colleague what browser they are using and what version of UBlock Origin they are using.

Additionally if you can have them follow these steps it’d be helpful for us to identify what list is flagging the CTAs.:
Within uBlock origin, could you click the plugin when it blocks our CTA script and then click the “logs” icon please? Within here if you find the cta script being blocked. In here there should be a single digit number within about the 5th Column. If you can click this this should bring up a details page which shows the filter that is blocking this script. If you can pass on screenshots of this this would be greatly helpful. There are also 2 other tabs on this page. If you can pass on screenshots of this it also should help us narrow down what specific list and setup is blocking this.
Will Do <@U7SL518D6> Thanks for doing a little diggin. My team really wants to use CTA’s but I have been hesitant because I have seen this issue

ok, he got back to me. He’s using uBlock Origin v1.29.2
Chrome Version 84.0.4147.135 (Official Build) (64-bit)
screenshots coming. in the meantime I will report to ublock
Thank you for these I’ll pass them along so we can see what we can do on our end to influence this. Ideall the root issue with this can be resolved, and not implement a band-aid fix.
Yep that's exactly what I had to do.
add custom class in DND_SECTION, DND_COLUMN and Dnd_row
